#!/usr/bin/env Rscript

# ==============================================================================
# Baseline and activated EBV TCR integration/clustering
# ==============================================================================
#
# Purpose:
#   This script runs the split downstream integration and clustering analyses for:
#     1. baseline EBV TCR object, and
#     2. activated/counterpart EBV TCR object.
#
#   It starts from the publication-ready TCR RDS objects generated by
#   9_TCR_multimer_QC.R:
#     - 1_EBV_baseline_TCR.rds
#     - 1_EBV_LCL_activated_TCR.rds
#
#   It performs:
#     - run/batch annotation,
#     - SCTransform,
#     - Harmony integration,
#     - clustering and UMAP,
#     - marker detection,
#     - contaminant cluster removal,
#     - illegitimate tetramer/sample filtering,
#     - re-integration after filtering,
#     - cluster reannotation,
#     - marker average-expression export, and
#     - module scoring for the baseline object.
#
# Notes:
#   - Paths are intentionally generic for GitHub.
#   - Update the config block before running.
#   - The baseline illegitimate tetramer filter is rule-based and writes the
#     flagged barcodes to disk. The activated workflow then removes the same
#     barcodes if present.
#
# ==============================================================================


# ----------------------------- #
# 0. Load packages
# ----------------------------- #

